INSTALLING LATEX FOR MAC OS

1. Install MacTex
An install package needed to run Tex on Mac.
http://tug.org/mactex/

2. Install Sublime Text
Text editor.
http://www.sublimetext.com/

3. Install Skim
PDF Viewer: helps you to synchronize between a line in a TeX source file and the generated output PDF file.
http://skim-app.sourceforge.net/

Alternative
Single installation: TeXPad
https://www.texpadapp.com

INSTALLING PACKAGE CONTROL (https://sublime.wbond.net/installation)
1. Open Sublime Text console: ctrl+'
2. Copy/Paste: import urllib.request,os,hashlib; h = '7183a2d3e96f11eeadd761d777e62404' + 'e330c659d4bb41d3bdf022e94cab3cd0'; pf = 'Package Control.sublime-package'; ipp = sublime.installed_packages_path(); urllib.request.install_opener( urllib.request.build_opener( urllib.request.ProxyHandler()) ); by = urllib.request.urlopen( 'http://sublime.wbond.net/' + pf.replace(' ', '%20')).read(); dh = hashlib.sha256(by).hexdigest(); print('Error validating download (got %s instead of %s), please try manual install' % (dh, h)) if dh != h else open(os.path.join( ipp, pf), 'wb' ).write(by)

INSTALLING LATEXING
1. In Sublime type: Command + Shift + P
2. Package Control: Install Package
3. LaTeXing

LINKS
http://docs.latexing.com/stable/introduction.html
http://economistry.com/2013/01/installing-and-using-latex-for-mac/

